==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cognominal
<hw>Cog*nom"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to a cognomen; of the nature of a surname.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cognominal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cognominal
<hw>Cog*nom"i*nal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One bearing the same name; a
namesake.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cognomination</ent>⟦br⟧
